auman, and Richard Tuttle, among others. As founder of the New Museum of Contemporary Art, she organized and curated groundbreaking exhibitions that often focused on the nexus of art and politics. The book highlights Tucker's commitment to forging a new system when the prevailing one proved too narrow for her expansive vision.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aART / General.2bisacsh  a1960s.  aamerican art.  aart and politics.  aart fanatics.  aart lovers.  aart world.  aart.  aartists.  abehind the scenes.  abiography autobiography.  acareer.  acontemporary art.  aengaging.  afemale authors.  afeminist movement.  alife changes.  amajor exhibitions.  amemoir.  amodern art.  amoney and power.  amuseum curator.  amuseums.  anew museum of contemporary art.  anew york art.  anew york city.  anew york.  anonfiction.  apainting and sculpture.  apaintings.  aretrospective.  awealth.  awomen.1 aLou, Liza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLou, Liza, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTucker, Marcia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025700940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094219640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942196423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942196/original  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY